item.description:
wontfix: <p>
Since in your own theme you don't have to worry about backwards-compatibility, you could force template-loader.php to call load_template():
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function force_load_template( $template ) {
	load_template( $template );
	return false;
}
add_filter( 'template_include', 'force_load_template', 999 );
</pre><p>
Re-closing as wontfix. Feel free to leave further comments, though.
</p>

invalid: <pre class="wiki">&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
   has-children
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;ul&gt;
   &lt;li&gt; children..
</pre><p>
like you suggest is invalid nested HTML.
</p>
<p>
The current form is the correct method for nested lists:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">&lt;ul&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;
   has-children
   &lt;ul&gt;
     &lt;li&gt; children..
</pre><p>
You can probably achieve what you want by having the child ul 100% width, and setting a padding on it instead of a margin, as a result, the background colour of the parent would be hidden behind the background colour of the child ul.
</p>
<p>
Closing as invalid due to the premise being the HTML is incorrect.
</p>
